 To convert $\frac{3}{8}$ into a decimal, we can divide the numerator (3) by the denominator (8) using long division. Here's how the calculation goes:

\[
\begin{array}{c|cccc}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & . & 3 & 7 & 5 \\
\cline{2-6}
8 & 3 & . & 0 & 0 & 0 \\
\multicolumn{2}{r}{2} & 4 & \downarrow & & \\ \cline{2-3}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & 6 & 0 \\
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & 5 & 6 & \\ \cline{3-4}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & & 4 & 0 \\
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & & 4 & 0 \\ \cline{4-5}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & & & 0 \\
\end{array}
\]

So, $\frac{3}{8} = 0.375$.

solution:
Since $\angle C = 45^\circ$, triangle $ACD$ is a $45^\circ$-$45^\circ$-$90^\circ$ triangle, which means $AD = CD = AC/\sqrt{2} = 3$.  Then $BD = BC - CD = 4 - 3 = 1$.

[asy]
unitsize(1 cm);

pair A, B, C, D, E, F, H;

A = (1,3);
